definitions.definition: Characterized by an unsophisticated focus on local concerns to the exclusion of wider contexts; elementary in scope or outlook.
examples: The use of simple, primary colors in the painting gave it a parochial feel.
Some people in the United States have been accused of taking a parochial view, of not being interested in international matters.

secondary_definitions: ( derogatory ) Characterized by an unsophisticated focus on local concerns to the exclusion of wider contexts; elementary in scope or outlook.
